<h3>Unintentional Sins</h3>
<p>Of all the methods Gd gave to us for atonement, the sacrifices were the weakest. (Please see below at â€˜There were other methodsâ€¦â€™). This is the case because sacrifices only made atonement for one kind of sin. Several verses seem to indicate that there needs to be a sacrifice in order to gain atonement for sins. But it must be pointed out just which sins are forgiven by these sacrifices: unintentional sins AND ONLY unintentional sins. This is stated repeatedly:</p>
<div class="bible-wrapper">
    <div class="bible-verse">
        <div class="bible-hebrew">  
